Hashtable over a set of elements, using Int as keys. On Flash and Javascript, the underlying structure is an Object.

Constructor

new()
Creates a new empty hashtable.

Instance Methods

exists(key : Int) : Bool

Tells if a value exists for the given key. In particular, it's useful to tells if a key has a null value versus no value.

get(key : Int) : Null<T>

Get a value for the given key.

iterator() : Iterator<T>

Returns an iterator of all values in the hashtable.

keys() : Iterator<Int>

Returns an iterator of all keys in the hashtable.

remove(key : Int) : Bool

Removes a hashtable entry. Returns true if there was such entry.

set(key : Int, value : T) : Void

Set a value for the given key.
